d, 'What is wrong with you?\"' I said, \"Let my parents be sacrificed for you! The people claim that all the deeds of Amir have been annulled.\" The Prophet (ﷺ) asked, \"Who said so?\" I replied, \"So-and-so and soand- so and Usaid bin Al-Hudair Al-Ansari said, 'Whoever says so is telling a lie. Verily, 'Amir will have double reward.\"' (While speaking) the Prophet (ﷺ) put two of his fingers together to indicate that, and added, \"He was really a hard-working man and a Mujahid (devout fighter in Allah's Cause) and rarely have there lived in it (i.e., Madina or the battle-field) an \"Arab like him.\""
